profile_positions.description:
Author, researcher and public advocate role relating to earthquake insurance claims as a result of the 2010-2012 earthquakes in Christchurch, New Zealand.

Books: 1) The Christchurch Fiasco and 2) The Insurance Aftershock
see https://vimeo.com/55403128


•	Technical expertise, claims resolution skills and knowledge of insurance and claims principles, practices and procedures. Researched public policy issues relating to insurance and wrote clearly to support policy advocacy, evaluated the effectiveness of existing insurance policies by conducting data gathering;
•	Provided advice and guidance to the community and politicians on the formulation of new policy directions and strategies for earthquake insurance, identifying and developing strategies to advance legislative and regulatory priorities; 
•	Served as a resource for the community identifying, evaluating and analyzing the impact of insurance initiatives including conducting legislative analysis;
•	 Developed strategic relationships with policymakers and community leaders to assist in shaping public policy initiatives. Drafted formal advice and opinions; 
•	Regular public speaker on insurance matters and regularly quoted by the media to comment on various aspects of insurance developments;
•	Contributed to other international publications on Disaster Management and was an invited speaker at conferences; 
•	'Lead' and worked directly on complex legal insurance litigation. Reviewing and evaluating cases and lawsuits.  Worked with a legal team to establish, communicate and implement a Litigation Plan. 

Core Competencies: insurance law, reinsurance, claims policy, claims settlement; public relations; human rights; legal research, writing, public speaking, negotiating, thought leadership, advocacy, government and institutional affairs, disaster management and sustainability.

Providing advice and counsel in real time to various business stakeholders, regarding a wide range of legal issues.

•	Proactively identify urgent legal and compliance issues of material concern to the company and work with leadership to identify appropriate direction and courses of action;
•	Support and help implement the objectives set by the Board and the General Counsel; 
•	Develop, draft and promulgate corporate due diligence practices with respect to acquisition targets, owners, business partners, suppliers, and consultants; 
•	Develop, draft, promulgate and maintain policies, standards and procedures. 

Core Competencies: Mergers and Acquisition, Joint Ventures, Restructuring, Company Secretarial, Due Diligence, Management of Corporate Entities, Governance, Standardization of Legal Documentation and Internal Policy, New Business Development, Contractual and Corporate Compliance.

Generalist role interfacing with multiple internal clients working closely and often cross-functionally  to provide practical legal advice and support across a range of business functions.

•	Interfaced with Project Finance, Global Clients, Loan Syndication, Emerging Markets, Financial Engineering, Asset Based Finance, Structured Lending, and Risk Management. 
•	Participated on cross-functional teams to develop and maintain Legal Obligations;
•	Collaborate with others to monitor changes in law and regulation;
•	Build and manage cross-enterprise product subject matter expertise e.g. in project finance;
•	Collaborate with appropriate product area lawyers to enhance consistency of legal positions;
•	Work with Compliance counterparts, as well as counterparts in Risk and Oversight and Controls, to identify and implement process changes to ensure compliance with state and local laws.
Member of the International Association and De Ring.


Core Competencies:  ISDA Master Agreements, Master Repurchase Agreements, Master Securities Forward Transaction Agreements and other industry standard trading agreements. LMA loan agreements, Corporate Lending and Inter-bank Loans, Custody, Intellectual Property, Bankruptcy, Euro Guarantees, General Terms and Conditions, Legislation and Regulation, Policy, Joint Ventures, Project Finance etc.
